The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | SA fined for slow over-rate
                                                   SA fined for slow over-rate
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: South Africa were fined on Monday for maintaining a slow over-rate in the drawn first Test against India. Match Referee Roshan Mahanama found South Africa were two overs short of its target .         
	According to the ICC code of conduct, players are fined five per cent of their match fees for every over their side fails to bowl in the allotted time, with the captain fined double that amount.                                                                                                                       
